ina. Drawing from interviews, participant observations, oral history, and archival research in a Miao and a Dong village-town in Qiandongnan Prefecture, Guizhou Province, this book examines the manifold and contradictory agendas that have captured rural ethnic schooling at a crossroads.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, RuralzChina, Southwest. 0aRural developmentzChina, Southwest. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Social Context of Education. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438460383423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438460383/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles